cardio.name: Running
cardio.description: Running is a method of terrestrial locomotion allowing humans and other animals to move rapidly on foot.

cardio.name: Cycling
cardio.description: Cycling, also called biking or bicycling, is the use of bicycles for transport, recreation, exercise or sport.

cardio.name: Swimming
cardio.description: Swimming is an individual or team sport that requires the use of one's entire body to move through water.

cardio.name: Jumping Jacks
cardio.description: Jumping jacks are a physical jumping exercise performed by jumping to a position with the legs spread wide and the hands touching overhead and then returning to a position with the feet together and the arms at the sides.

cardio.name: Burpees
cardio.description: The burpee, or squat thrust, is a full body exercise used in strength training and as an aerobic exercise.

cardio.name: High Knees
cardio.description: High knees is a high-intensity exercise that works your major muscle groups.

cardio.name: Mountain Climbers
cardio.description: Mountain climbers are a great total body exercise. You use your core because you are stabilizing your body.
